{
  "stem": "18778.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 188.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the was like a godsend when the Germans declared they were preparing a ship that would leave for Cuba in May of 1939, and that it would be specifically for Jewish refugees who wanted to leave Germany.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so my father immediately got in touch with a travel agency and booked passage.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And-- and that's how we came to be on the Louis.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It-- I don't know how they heard about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Perhaps it was publicized in the paper or perhaps it was through these Cuban friends.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know how they heard about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there it was, you know?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the minute they heard it-- sometimes these thing go by word of mouth when somebody hears about something like that, because there were such few ships that took Jews all together.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In my papers, for instance, I found out that most ships which left Germany at that time in history had only a limited amount of space that they reserved for Jews, so that even if you had all the necessary papers to leave, finding a ship to take you, a means of getting out, was still a problem.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And here was a ship that was entirely for Jewish refugees, so that was quite something.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Of course, there was an ulterior motive for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this motive really is one that we didn't find out until the authors of the book found evidence that this was to be a-- a trip for an espionage situation, and the Germans figured, let the Jews pay for it.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was something none of us knew at the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was-- it was a very complicated matter to do this.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
